[SN]TITLE[SN]
Luke Waterfall: Lincoln City captain signs new contract

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Lincoln City captain Luke Waterfall has signed a new two-year contract with the National League champions.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 26-year-old defender was out of contract following the club's title-winning season but has joined keeper Paul Farman in signing a new deal.
He started 44 of Lincoln's 46 league games as they clinched the championship with a further seven appearances in their FA Cup run to the quarter-finals.
Waterfall, who joined from Wrexham in June 2015, also scored seven goals.
